    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-06-11T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-06-11T12:00:00-05:00" n="701"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d701">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/6983: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the High
                        Commissioner at Constantinople</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-06-11T13:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 11, 1920—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>72. For Admiral McCully.</p>
                <p>Your 55, June 1st.<note n="18" xml:id="d701fn18">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_601">p. 601</ref>.</note> Is
                    Department to understand that Wrangel’s negotiations with Soviets, proposed by
                    British, look to mere armistice with continuation Wrangel’s control of Crimea,
                    or extension of Soviet rule over Crimea with amnesty to Wrangel’s forces?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
